column1: # Compiled by Dhvanil Desai using 2013-2017 ASAS-SN Bright Supernova Catalogues from Holoien et al. (2017a
# DiscMag          Discovery V-band or g-band Magnitude
# DiscAge          Age of supernova at discovery
# Recovered        Was the supernova recovered by ASAS-SN?
# MagV_corrected   PeakMagV corrected for Galactic extinction and K-corrections
# dist_mod         Distance modulus computed using the Redshift
# abs_M_peak       Absolute peak V-band magnitude (MagV_corrected - dist_mod)
# comp_SNIa        Completeness correction factor for a supernova of given apparent and absolute magnitude
# weighted_N       The total weight for each supernova (1 / (comp_SNIa * F2_SNIa))
# Note: This table is limited to supernovae brighter than 16.5 mag in the V-band with the correction factors computed using a maximum redshift of 0.07.
